===Etymology===
{{L.}} [[praenomen]] ''[[Marcus]]'', derived from ''[[Mars]]'', the Roman god of war, originally ''[[Mavors]]'', from ''*Māwort-''.

===Proper noun===
'''Mark'''
# A male [[given name]] meaning "Warrior".
# (''Bible'') [[w:Mark the Evangelist|Mark the Evangelist]], also called John Mark, first patriarch of Alexandria and credited with the authorship of the Gospel of Mark.
# The [[w:Gospel of Mark|Gospel of Mark]], the second of the four [[gospel]]s, a [[book]] attributed to Mark the Evangelist.

